results.name: The number of non-unitary divisors in the conjugated prime factorization of n: a(n) = A048105(A122111(n)).
comment: Equally, the number of divisors in the conjugated prime factorization of n minus the number of its unitary divisors.
Note that A001221(A122111(n)) = A001221(n) for all n.
